oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Moonshine still at Fredonia Mountain
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of four men at a moonshine still on the rear of Fredonia Mountain, near Little Brush Creek. Three of the men have scratched out their faces on the original photograph. The man's face who is visible was wanted for murder.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Stills (Distilleries); Rifles; Barrels; Hand tools
